<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1107">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Un3/3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                Rice</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 733]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform you
                            that complaint has been made to the Department concerning the frequent
                            appearance on the streets of Detroit of uniformed Canadian soldiers
                            wearing filled cartridge belts.</p>
                        <p>It is hoped that this matter may be called to the attention of the
                            Canadian Government and that such instructions may be issued as are
                            necessary to prevent the continuance of this practice.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>